overview: The British Rock Symphony was a tour that featured classic rock hits presented by a gospel choir, a full orchestra and vocalists including: Roger Daltrey, Darlene Love, Nikki Lamborn, Alice Cooper, Paul Young, Simon Townshend and Gary Brooker. Geoff Whitehorn played guitar and Zak Starkey performed on drums with Jaz Lochrie on Bass guitar.  1	Jumping Jack Flash  2	Imagine  3	Blackbird  4	Come Together  5	Kashmir  6	Norwegian Wood  7	Street Fighting Man  8	Start Me Up  9	5:15  10	Ruby Tuesday  11	Stairway To Heaven  12	Conquistador  13	A Whiter Shade Of Pale  14	Let It Be  15	Pinball Wizard  16	You Better You Bet  17	Who Are You  18	With A Little Help From My Friends
title: British Rock Symphony
